  "texts": [
    "Although many AI models show promising results in computational simulations, their effectiveness in real-world settings remains uncertain without empirical validation.",
    "Sensory panels, chemical assays, and human participant trials are necessary to determine whether AI-generated predictions reflect actual perceptual and biological responses.",
    "Models that lack such validation may yield outputs that are not reliable or generalizable across populations or conditions.",
    "This issue is particularly relevant in areas such as health diagnostics, personalized nutrition, and food product development, where the accuracy of sensory predictions has direct practical consequences.",
    "To improve scientific rigor and user confidence, AI development should be closely integrated with experimental testing."
  ],
